						               													<description>It is a baseball card game that anyone can easily enjoy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Various tactical cards reflecting baseball elements&amp;#10;- Easy game rules&amp;#10;Hits or home runs if the pitcher and batter numbers match&amp;#10;- Player stats&amp;#10;Game management using each player's stats&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#160; They are divided into home team and away team.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#161; Select the first hit.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#162; The attacking player mixes 16 batter cards and the defending player mixes 16 pitcher cards and arranges them as shown in the picture.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#163; Each player draws 5 cards from the top of the deck and holds them invisible to the other side.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game progress&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#160; Each player turns one player card over and puts it in front.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#161; The player playing the batter card shouts &amp;ldquo;hit&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;home run&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#162; The player cards are turned over and compared.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When you shout &amp;ldquo;hit&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;If there is a match between the batter card and the pitcher card being compared, it is a hit. (2 numbers match double, 3 numbers match triple) If there is no match, the batter is out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When you shout &amp;ldquo;home run&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;If the number in the circle of the batter card being compared and the number of the pitcher card match even one, it becomes a home run. If there are no matching numbers, the batter is out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#163; The used cards are stacked on the used card pile, and the number of cards used from the new card pile is taken from the top to continue playing while maintaining 5 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#164; At 3 outs, they change their karate and play with the same rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#165; The player who attacked immediately before writes the points earned in the inning on the scoreboard.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#166; If you run out of cards while playing, shuffle the cards you used and reuse them.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#167; You can use only one tactical card. (Tactic cards used with player cards are turned over so that the opponent cannot see them and placed next to the player cards being compared.)&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#168; The player with the most points wins at the end of the set inning.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
